INNER LOOP SETUP
======================================================================

Iteration: 15
Backend: evolved
Reasoning: Iteration 15: Adopt trained-roofline architecture + MoE/quantization fixes.

**What Changed**:
- Complete rewrite of evolved_model.go to use trained-roofline's 7-term formula:
  β₁·max(T_pf_compute, T_pf_kv) + β₂·max(T_dc_compute, T_dc_kv) + β₃·T_weight
  + β₄·T_tp + β₅·L + β₆·batchSize + β₇
- Added InterleaveMoELayerStep/DenseIntermediateDim handling (#877 fix for Scout)
- Added EffectiveWeightBytesPerParam (FP8-aware, Scout uses 1 byte/param not 2)
- Added FP8 peak FLOPS selection for FP8 models on FP8-capable GPUs
- PostDecodeFixedOverhead now returns α₁ (was 0 in iter0-14)
- QueueingTime now returns constant α₀ (was α₀ + α₁×tokens + β₆ in iter0-14)
- Coefficient count: 7 betas + 3 alphas (was 8 betas + 3 alphas in iter14)

**Why This Architecture**:
Diagnostic analysis revealed two structural bugs in iter0-14's evolved model:
1. Missing memory-bandwidth floor: decode used compute-only formula, 13× too low at B=1
2. Per-request overhead accumulation: β₃/β₇ in StepTime accumulated O(N×B) per request
The trained-roofline backend (same codebase, 7% MAPE) avoids both. Iter15 adopts it
with enhancements for the current dataset (MoE interleave, FP8 quantization).

**Previous Iteration (14)**:
- Loss 2319% (catastrophic) — β₅ fix worked but structural E2E bug remained
- E2E RMSE 91% across ALL experiments due to phantom overhead accumulation

